Dialogue: 0,0:00:-01.00,0:00:00.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inherited will...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.64,0:00:03.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The tide of the times...\NPeople's dreams...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.54,0:00:06.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These things cannot be stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.38,0:00:09.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as people\Nseek the answer of freedom,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.48,0:00:17.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,these things will never cease to be!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.03,0:00:27.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I only believe in the future --\NI don't care if anyone laughs
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.20,0:00:32.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That racing passion makes you shine
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.54,0:00:38.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too bright,\Nbut I want to gaze at it
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.54,0:00:42.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sense "aesthetics" somewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.15,0:00:45.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really really stuck on you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.55,0:00:51.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I follow, follow in the footsteps\Nof a dream that resembles no one
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.99,0:00:55.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until I dramatically get it
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.33,0:01:03.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Believe In Wonderland!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.14,0:01:10.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to catch, catch the shape\Nof a dream no one can see
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.44,0:01:16.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to go with you,\Nso passionate feelings
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.58,0:01:19.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really\Nneed everything to add up
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.59,0:01:22.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rather than run-of-the-mill daily life,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.76,0:01:26.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,run for paradise instead
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.36,0:01:34.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Believe In Wonderland!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.07,0:01:40.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We found an island!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.84,0:01:42.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An island?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.21,0:01:44.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! An island! We found an island!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.54,0:01:48.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Nami! Good for you!\NThere's an island! You can get better!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.38,0:01:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's an island! An island! Island!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.48,0:01:57.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Island! Island!\N--Just go look.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.09,0:02:03.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An island!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.43,0:02:07.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All this snow! I'm so happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.67,0:02:14.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's far enough, pirates!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.61,0:02:16.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. I found people.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.68,0:02:21.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... they don't seem too friendly...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.38,0:02:26.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attention, pirates! Leave this\Nplace at once! This instant!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.95,0:02:29.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We came to find a doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.19,0:02:30.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have a sick person onboard!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.56,0:02:35.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We won't fall for that trick,\Nyou filthy pirates!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.53,0:02:38.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They really hate our guts.\NAnd we've just met, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.76,0:02:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't talk back!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.30,0:02:41.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're shooting!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.10,0:02:42.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't just do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.00,0:02:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Bastard!\N--Stop, Sanji-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.18,0:03:06.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"An Island Without Doctors?\NAdventure in a Nameless Land!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.53,0:03:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vivi!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.03,0:03:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, you--!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.77,0:03:20.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aim!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.61,0:03:23.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.11,0:03:25.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fighting won't help anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.28,0:03:30.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine! It only grazed my arm!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.98,0:03:35.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, we won't land here!\NBut could we ask for a doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.79,0:03:41.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our friend is suffering from a grave illness.\NPlease help! I beg you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.46,0:03:42.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vivi!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.80,0:03:46.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not fit to be captain, Luffy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.27,0:03:52.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not everything can be fixed\Nby acting recklessly!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.74,0:04:00.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you start a fight here,\Nwhat will happen to Nami-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.39,0:04:12.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I'm sorry! I was wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.73,0:04:14.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please call a doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.89,0:04:22.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please help our friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.67,0:04:31.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will show you to the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.71,0:04:39.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.19,0:04:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? They understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.02,0:04:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! You're amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.67,0:05:04.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must warn you, the only doctor\Nwe have here is a witch.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.28,0:05:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Witch?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.14,0:05:08.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You gotta be kidding me.\NNothing here makes sense...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.65,0:05:13.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this place, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.25,0:05:16.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This land still does not have a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.16,0:05:23.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A nameless land?\NDoes that really happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.30,0:05:25.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A bear!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.13,0:05:29.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone! Pretend to be dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.60,0:05:32.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Hiking Bear. They pose no danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.47,0:05:40.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't forget to bow.\NIt's proper hiking manners.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.61,0:05:43.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! All better now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.28,0:05:46.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.55,0:05:49.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I can finally do\Nsome real training!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.76,0:05:53.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was getting sick of\Nthat watered-down training,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.43,0:05:57.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and just watching the ship\Nis boring as hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.80,0:06:05.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'll go for some cold-weather\Nswimming to suppress my self.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.64,0:06:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is our village, Big Horn.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.08,0:06:13.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are weird animals\Nwalking everywhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.48,0:06:15.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's snow country for ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.55,0:06:20.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nami-san! We made it to a village\Nwith people! It's a village!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.49,0:06:23.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Thanks for the help, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.09,0:06:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those who aren't guards\Ncan return to their work.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.06,0:06:30.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, will you be alright by yourself,\NDalton-san? They're pirates!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.10,0:06:32.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe they pose no threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.80,0:06:35.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's my hunch of many years\Nof experience. You can trust it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.33,0:06:36.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.57,0:06:39.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's what Dalton-san says, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.17,0:06:42.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--And they don't seem dangerous...\N--Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.77,0:06:45.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, Dalton-san!\NWe leave the rest to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.34,0:06:47.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be ever careful, Dalton-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.35,0:06:52.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just call us again if anything happens!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.28,0:06:54.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They weren't this land's security forces?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.55,0:06:55.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're ordinary citizens.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.85,0:06:59.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to my home for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.39,0:07:02.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Look, Luffy! A Hiking Bear!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.03,0:07:02.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.00,0:07:04.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Oh, Dalton-san!\N--Gotta bow.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.46,0:07:07.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard there were pirates!\NAre you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.57,0:07:12.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, everything is okay.\NThere's nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.91,0:07:16.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Dalton-kun! I look forward\Nto the election in two days!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.01,0:07:20.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone says they're\Ngoing to vote for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.11,0:07:28.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-you can't be serious!\NI'm nothing but a sinful man!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.76,0:07:37.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Use that bed there.\NI'll warm the place up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.80,0:07:39.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't told you my name yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.67,0:07:43.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Dalton, captain of the\Nsecurity squad of this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.50,0:07:46.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please forgive our heavy-handed welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.84,0:07:49.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,May I ask you a question?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.07,0:07:50.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.71,0:07:54.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I somehow feel like I've seen you before.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.78,0:07:57.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-it's probably just your imagination!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.45,0:08:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, please tell us about this witch!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.05,0:08:04.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nami-san's temperature was 42° C\Nwhen I checked it just now!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.62,0:08:06.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,42°?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.73,0:08:09.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her fever's gone up for\Nthree days in a row.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.70,0:08:12.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She'll die if it goes up any more!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.40,0:08:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.60,0:08:18.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we don't even know the cause of\Nher illness, or how to treat it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.34,0:08:23.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need a doctor! Anyone will do!\NWhere is this witch of yours?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.24,0:08:26.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The witch, huh. Do you see those\Nmountains outside the window?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.98,0:08:30.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, those insanely tall--
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.62,0:08:32.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyper Snowman!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.75,0:08:35.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Snowzilla, the snow beast!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.15,0:08:36.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.36,0:08:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make me kick your asses!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.16,0:08:43.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those mountains are known\Nas the Drum Rockies.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.40,0:08:48.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you see the castle at the top\Nof the tallest one in the middle?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.20,0:08:49.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Castle?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.27,0:08:51.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--That castle no longer has its king.\N--That warms me up...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.97,0:08:54.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, there it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.34,0:08:56.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's so important about the castle?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.07,0:08:59.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only doctor in the land,\NDr. Kureha, lives there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.01,0:09:02.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People call her a witch.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.95,0:09:07.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! Of all the places,\Nwhy does it have to be so far away?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.29,0:09:09.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then call her here right away!\NWe have a critical patient!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.96,0:09:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we wanted to,\Nthere's no way to contact her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.36,0:09:16.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?! And she calls herself a doctor?!\NWhat the hell is she like?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.80,0:09:19.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a doctor, she's very skilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.63,0:09:24.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But she's an eccentric old hag.\NShe's nearly 140 years old now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.07,0:09:25.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.07,0:09:27.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,140?! I think she might need help!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.97,0:09:31.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And, let's see...\NShe likes pickled plums.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.21,0:09:35.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happens when people\Nhere get sick or injured?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.31,0:09:37.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She comes down from the\Nmountain when she feels like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.92,0:09:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She looks for patients,\Ntreats them, then, as payment,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.92,0:09:44.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she takes whatever she wants\Nfrom their houses before leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.82,0:09:47.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like an unfriendly old hag!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.33,0:09:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! She almost sounds like a pirate!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.66,0:09:53.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how does such an old\Nwoman go down that mountain?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.70,0:09:55.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an odd rumor...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.93,0:09:58.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but several people claim to have seen her
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.00,0:10:05.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,riding a sleigh through\Nthe sky on moonlit nights...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.78,0:10:09.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's the reason\Nshe's called a witch...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.15,0:10:15.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some also saw her with a strange\Ncreature they'd never seen before...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.19,0:10:19.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it! See? It's a Snow Man!\NIt's a snowy mountain, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.59,0:10:21.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew there'd be one!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.49,0:10:26.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A witch and a Snow Man?!\NOh, please never let us run into them!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.30,0:10:32.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She is the only doctor, but she's\Na hag I'd prefer to stay away from.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.20,0:10:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All we can do is wait for the next\Ntime she comes down the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.61,0:10:36.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.98,0:10:42.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit! We can't wait for that!\NEven as we speak, Nami-san is--!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.31,0:10:45.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Nami! Nami! Can you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.12,0:10:50.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.19,0:10:52.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! She's awake!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.79,0:10:55.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, the only way to see a\Ndoctor is to climb a mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.93,0:10:57.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna climb it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.16,0:10:59.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.26,0:11:02.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be crazy!\NWhat are you doing with Nami?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.43,0:11:04.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay! I'll carry her on my back!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.27,0:11:06.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That'll only make things even worse!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.77,0:11:09.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the problem?\NWe need to hurry, don't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.54,0:11:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true, but you can't!\NLook at how steep and tall it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.68,0:11:14.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.48,0:11:17.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you can make it,\Nbut it'd be too hard on Nami-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.85,0:11:21.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, look! If we fall,\Nwe'll land in snow!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.05,0:11:24.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even a healthy person would die\Ninstantly after a fall from there!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.39,0:11:29.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously! She's 6° C\Nover normal temperature!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.26,0:11:37.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you even get it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.17,0:11:42.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to get over this fast...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.44,0:11:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to hurry... for Vivi...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.48,0:11:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you, Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.22,0:12:04.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's more like it!\NJust leave it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.01,0:12:20.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe it!\NLike captain, like navigator!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.28,0:12:22.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what condition\Nyou're in, Nami-san?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.65,0:12:25.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you'll be okay?\NIt'll take hours to get there!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.52,0:12:27.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old guy! Meat! Gimme meat!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.42,0:12:29.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meat?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.79,0:12:31.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! I'm comin' too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.59,0:12:36.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Luffy! Don't fall even once,\Nor you can expect Nami to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.29,0:12:38.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! Even once?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.13,0:12:42.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Hold still!\NI need to tie this right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.93,0:12:44.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All set.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.20,0:12:48.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'm going to wait here.\NI'd only get in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.37,0:12:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Same here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.37,0:12:51.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.14,0:12:53.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Nami! Hold on tight!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.98,0:12:57.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.42,0:13:00.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're really set on going...\NI won't stop you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.99,0:13:03.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But at least climb up from the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.56,0:13:06.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are Lapins on this course.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.66,0:13:08.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fierce, carnivorous rabbits.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.99,0:13:12.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you encounter a pack of them,\Nyou're as good as dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.16,0:13:14.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rabbits? But we're in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.70,0:13:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should be fine. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.43,0:13:18.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! I'll kick 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.10,0:13:21.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kick?! You can't be serious!\NYou'd be walking to your deaths!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.51,0:13:22.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.77,0:13:25.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, then! Let's go, Sanji!\NBefore Nami dies!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.68,0:13:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! Don't say things that\Ncould jinx us, you dumbass!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.05,0:13:34.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will they really be all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.75,0:13:38.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm not worried about those two...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.06,0:13:41.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the question is if Nami-san's\Nstrength will last long enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.86,0:13:49.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope they make it there safely...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.41,0:13:57.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.34,0:14:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come inside. It's cold out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.05,0:14:03.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's okay.\NI want to stay outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.15,0:14:10.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.16,0:14:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.16,0:14:25.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I will join you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.18,0:14:41.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We did have some, long ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.82,0:14:43.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.05,0:14:47.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctors. But they're all gone now,\Nfor certain reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.76,0:14:50.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were all incredibly skilled...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.90,0:14:54.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were even known as\Nan advanced medical nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.77,0:14:58.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.47,0:15:03.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This country was destroyed\Njust a few months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.58,0:15:05.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the hands of pirates!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.31,0:15:09.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Eh?!\N--The entire country?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.25,0:15:12.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why you were so nervous about us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.15,0:15:17.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The word "pirate" is still\Ntoo much for everyone to handle...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.56,0:15:20.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.69,0:15:23.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there were only five\Npeople in that pirate group.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.66,0:15:25.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The captain called himself "Blackbeard,"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.80,0:15:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and he destroyed our country\Nin the blink of an eye
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.23,0:15:32.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with his devastating power...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.17,0:15:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only five pirates?!\NYou can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.47,0:15:37.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blackbeard?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.11,0:15:40.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there are some who say it was\Nactually good for the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.78,0:15:43.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing good about\Na country being destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.11,0:15:47.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! That's the stupidest\Nthing I've ever heard!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.55,0:15:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.79,0:15:53.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But people say that because the\Nmonarchy that existed here until then
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.86,0:15:57.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was appalling in the eyes of the citizens.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.06,0:16:00.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The country's former name\Nwas the Drum Kingdom!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.43,0:16:03.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The king's name was Wapol!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.33,0:16:10.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was the worst king possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.11,0:16:12.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! That man! I remember him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.01,0:16:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wapol?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.25,0:16:25.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's gotten a little colder.\NThe wind's picking up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.79,0:16:30.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So why aren't you wearing shoes?!\NJust seeing that is painful!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.09,0:16:31.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my police!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.83,0:16:34.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Police?! You mean "policy"!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.43,0:16:37.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.57,0:16:41.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, did you know?\NPeople in snowy countries never sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.54,0:16:43.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Why's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.11,0:16:45.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,'Cause they'll die if they go to sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.48,0:16:47.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid!\NThere's nobody like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.98,0:16:53.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the truth!\NSomeone told me a long time ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.08,0:16:54.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Usopp, I bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.19,0:16:58.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I heard it in a pub in my village!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.12,0:17:03.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why did that Dalton guy have a bed?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.09,0:17:04.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a good point.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.76,0:17:09.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's for when he dies, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.60,0:17:13.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.24,0:17:15.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, did you know this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.81,0:17:19.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Women in snowy lands\Nall have silky-smooth skin!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.04,0:17:20.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.08,0:17:21.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.65,0:17:25.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whenever you're cold,\Nyou rub your skin for warmth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.12,0:17:27.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you get smooth skin.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.59,0:17:33.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So women in snowy places have\Nsuch silky-smooth, white skin!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.16,0:17:35.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How come it's white?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.23,0:17:40.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because the color of the\Nconstantly-falling snow dyes their skin!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.77,0:17:43.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?! You're so dumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.13,0:17:45.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like you're really anyone to talk!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.40,0:17:47.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.37,0:17:49.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...quit being so damn annoying!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.47,0:17:54.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was with that guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.78,0:18:00.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there, Nami-san!\NWe're gonna get you to a doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.55,0:18:02.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The snow's really deep around here...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.89,0:18:04.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Luffy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.29,0:18:12.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Run more smoothly!\NYou're gonna make Nami-san worse!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.97,0:18:15.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-what are these?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.63,0:18:20.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're white and big,\Nso they're polar bears! I'm sure of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.51,0:18:24.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! You know Wapol?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.11,0:18:29.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't just know him!\NHe's the pirate who attacked our ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.75,0:18:31.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got rid of him, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.98,0:18:35.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I do recall him saying\Nsomething about the Drum Kingdom...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.42,0:18:36.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.65,0:18:39.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no question about it!\NI remember clearly now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.59,0:18:44.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I met him once at a monarch\Nmeeting my father took me to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.53,0:18:47.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when I was very young!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.53,0:18:49.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monarch meeting?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.60,0:18:51.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.60,0:18:54.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, uhh, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.27,0:19:00.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, we met Wapol!\NYesterday, on our way here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.18,0:19:03.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday?! Are you sure?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.11,0:19:09.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what's going on, then?!\NHe called himself a pirate, not a king!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.29,0:19:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He must be calling himself\Nthat as camouflage.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.36,0:19:16.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wapol is merely wandering the sea,\Ntrying to return to this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.63,0:19:20.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the people on that ship were\Nkicked out because they were no match
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.63,0:19:24.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for the Blackbeard Pirates\Nwhen they attacked this country?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.40,0:19:27.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No match? It's not like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.07,0:19:28.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.04,0:19:33.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When it happened, Wapol's army\Ndidn't even try to fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.81,0:19:37.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, the moment he learned\Nhow strong the pirates were,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.12,0:19:43.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wapol abandoned the country and was\Nthe very first to flee out to sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.05,0:19:46.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That threw the entire nation into despair.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.59,0:19:48.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this what the king--
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.26,0:19:51.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what the king of\Nan entire country does?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.66,0:19:57.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's appalling!\NA king abandoning his people!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.50,0:19:58.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vivi...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.74,0:20:00.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're exactly right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.84,0:20:04.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But at least Wapol's\Ntyranny is finally over.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.78,0:20:07.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The remaining people on this\Nisland have come together
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.28,0:20:10.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to try to create a new country.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.85,0:20:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what we most fear right\Nnow is Wapol's return...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.75,0:20:17.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The return of his monarchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.76,0:20:21.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We must avoid that at all costs,\Nwhile people are still feeling unsure!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.63,0:20:29.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we're to create a new,\Npeaceful nation on this island!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.27,0:20:38.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It jumped!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.18,0:20:40.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You gotta be kidding me!\NHow can it move like that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.65,0:20:43.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--What is it, a gorilla?!\N--No! A polar bear!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.35,0:20:44.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a bunny!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.65,0:20:46.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who just\Ncalled it a gorilla...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.65,0:20:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These must be the Lapins that\NDalton was talking about!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.39,0:20:55.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This many of them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.86,0:20:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.33,0:21:01.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Wapol-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.13,0:21:05.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Chess?\NDid you find Straw Hat's ship?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.17,0:21:09.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Wapol-sama!\NWe've finally returned home!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.11,0:21:10.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.07,0:21:13.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How many months have passed\Nas we've wandered the sea?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.81,0:21:17.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's our homeland! The Drum Kingdom!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.12,0:21:25.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Truly?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.77,0:21:45.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The world is awfully big
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.24,0:21:48.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so even if there is treasure somewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.55,0:21:51.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the odds are astronomical
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.95,0:21:58.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So relying on dumb luck\Nwon't get you anywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.09,0:22:01.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So even,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.89,0:22:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if someone stops me or\Nlaughs at me from the shadows
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.63,0:22:11.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the ship will continue forward
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.84,0:22:13.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bon voyage!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.94,0:22:15.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget about them!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.24,0:22:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know I'm a fool,\Nbut I gotta go
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.95,0:22:28.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The crazier the dream,\Nthe cooler the ambition
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.62,0:22:35.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know I'm a fool,\Nbut I'm gonna fight
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.29,0:22:42.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The farther the sea,\Nthe more heavenly it surely is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.30,0:22:43.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do everything you can,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.63,0:22:51.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and you'll get a little nearer to any horizon
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.15,0:22:59.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Luffy!\NDon't you dare fight these guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.28,0:22:59.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.85,0:23:02.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nami-san will feel\Nthe whole impact and die!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.65,0:23:05.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! I won't fight!\NBut, what do I do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.16,0:23:08.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just dodge! Dodge and run!\NBut don't retreat!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.53,0:23:10.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.09,0:23:12.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! The witch is\Nin the next town over?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.00,0:23:14.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next episode of One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.10,0:23:16.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Are You Happy?\NThe Doctor Called Witch!"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.77,0:23:24.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
